<article>
    <h1>MALAYSIA: NITA COS&#xAD;MET&#xAD;ICS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201106/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-06"><time>2020-11-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The make-up brand pays tribute to its Malaysian roots with quirk­ily named prod­ucts – like its Warung Col­lec­tion lip­sticks ($20), which are named af­ter lo­cal drinks Ban­dung, Kopi Susu and Teh Tarik.</p>
    <p>The brand was founded by Malaysian cre­ative Aznita Az­man in 2016, with a fo­cus on in­clu­sive prod­uct ranges and rep­re­sent­ing her her­itage. It now boasts more than 60,000 fol­low­ers on In­sta­gram.</p>
    <p>Prod­ucts are hy­poal­ler­genic, ve­gan, paraben-free, sul­phate-free, al­co­hol-free and cru­elty-free.</p>
    <p>Avail­able here via SocietyA, Nita Cos­met­ics was se­lected for its “di­verse range of prod­ucts that are af­ford­able and suit­able for all skin tones”, says the fash­ion and beauty re­tailer’s gen­eral man­ager Lily Hamid. “Nita Cos­met­ics is an art­ful blend of Malaysia’s rich cul­tures and tra­di­tions, some­thing that Sin­ga­pore­ans can re­late to.”</p>
    <p>Avail­able at SocietyA Beauty (so­ci­ety-a.com/brand/nita)</p>

